00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:02,360
But.

483
00:26:03,125 --> 00:26:04,505
I don't think it changed our timeline,

484
00:26:05,086 --> 00:26:07,047
and it was totally worth it, because it got us

485
00:26:07,087 --> 00:26:08,507
to our final product faster.

486
00:26:09,127 --> 00:26:12,709
By having outside consultants come in and give notes

487
00:26:12,769 --> 00:26:15,690
on our scripts, we were able to get through things faster.

488
00:26:16,651 --> 00:26:19,752
And having the DDML compiler made it easy for us

489
00:26:19,812 --> 00:26:22,494
to listen to them and make changes

490
00:26:22,554 --> 00:26:24,114
based on their suggestions.

491
00:26:25,675 --> 00:26:31,337
Also, one of our consultants for the game happened to be this like kinda popular famous

